  const token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
  if (!token || !verifyJwt(token)) return res.status(401).json({ error: 'unauthorized' });
  next();
}
app.get('/users', requireAuth, (req, res) => { /* ... */ });
```

## 4. Listening on all interfaces with no TLS (A02: Cryptographic Failures)

`app.listen(3000)` binds to `0.0.0.0` and speaks plain HTTP. In production this should be behind a TLS-terminating proxy (nginx, ALB) or use `https.createServer`. Also consider binding to `127.0.0.1` if only a local proxy should reach it:

```js
app.listen(3000, '127.0.0.1', () => { ... });
```

## 5. No CORS policy defined (A05)

Without explicit CORS, browsers apply same-origin defaults, but as soon as a frontend is added this is usually loosened incorrectly (`*`). Define an allowlist up front:

```js
